1
00:00:05,530 --> 00:00:07,470
Sir.

2
00:00:08,509 --> 00:00:10,829
Sir!

3
00:00:10,829 --> 00:00:12,829
Sir.

4
00:00:12,830 --> 00:00:13,730
Open your eyes.

5
00:00:13,730 --> 00:00:14,380
Sir!

6
00:00:14,379 --> 00:00:15,699
What happened here, sir?

7
00:00:15,699 --> 00:00:17,259
Go start the car first.

8
00:00:17,259 --> 00:00:19,079
- Hurry!
- Yes, sir.

9
00:00:19,079 --> 00:00:20,249
Okay.

10
00:00:20,249 --> 00:00:22,829
Sir!

11
00:00:22,829 --> 00:00:25,559
Sir, wake up, please.

12
00:00:25,559 --> 00:00:27,009
You have to hang in there.

13
00:00:27,009 --> 00:00:28,449
You have to live.

14
00:00:28,448 --> 00:00:30,538
You must live.

15
00:00:34,458 --> 00:00:36,498
Since his stomach was pumped in time

16
00:00:36,499 --> 00:00:38,659
- he will live.
- Okay.

17
00:00:38,658 --> 00:00:40,008
Rather than focusing
on his physical status

18
00:00:40,009 --> 00:00:42,959
he has to be mentally stable.

19
00:00:42,958 --> 00:00:44,648
We understand.

20
00:00:44,648 --> 00:00:46,908
- Thank you.
- Thank you.

21
00:00:49,597 --> 00:00:51,757
When he wakes up

22
00:00:52,608 --> 00:00:55,138
we have to give him a hope to live.

23
00:00:55,138 --> 00:00:58,068
In order to do that,
we have to find out the truth fast.

24
00:00:58,067 --> 00:01:00,857
But we have no idea
where this victim is.

25
00:01:00,857 --> 00:01:02,857
I agree.

26
00:01:02,857 --> 00:01:05,057
- Manager Gu.
- Yes?

27
00:01:05,057 --> 00:01:07,717
Contact the reporters now.

28
00:01:07,717 --> 00:01:09,007
Pardon?

29
00:01:09,007 --> 00:01:11,767
Tell them I will have an
interview at the company.

30
00:01:11,767 --> 00:01:14,107
What kind of interview will  it be?

31
00:01:16,706 --> 00:01:19,996
A can't miss opportunity.

32
00:01:24,436 --> 00:01:26,756
<i>You probably won't find him.</i>

33
00:01:26,756 --> 00:01:31,946
<i>I'm certain that he was
cast by Kang Dong Suk.</i>

34
00:01:33,135 --> 00:01:35,055
As a representative of this company

35
00:01:35,056 --> 00:01:39,556
I'll share our position on this matter.

36
00:01:39,555 --> 00:01:42,335
As for the food poisoning case

37
00:01:42,334 --> 00:01:43,944
it was staged.

38
00:01:43,945 --> 00:01:45,735
Staged?

39
00:01:45,735 --> 00:01:49,265
By someone who was trying
to harm our company and Soon Jin Dairy

40
00:01:49,265 --> 00:01:50,755
it was his conspiracy.

41
00:01:50,754 --> 00:01:52,754
Do you have any grounds
for this allegation?

42
00:01:52,755 --> 00:01:53,895
If you say that without any evidence

43
00:01:53,895 --> 00:01:55,435
it could create more problems.

44
00:01:55,434 --> 00:01:58,914
I have something more
positive than evidence.

45
00:01:58,914 --> 00:02:00,224
Right now

46
00:02:00,224 --> 00:02:06,164
we have the person who collapsed
after drinking the rotten milk.

47
00:02:06,163 --> 00:02:08,383
What is he saying?

48
00:02:09,773 --> 00:02:12,553
He is under our care right now.

49
00:02:12,553 --> 00:02:17,573
He also confessed that this case
was orchestrated by someone.

50
00:02:17,572 --> 00:02:18,642
If that's true

51
00:02:18,642 --> 00:02:20,132
where is that person now?

52
00:02:20,133 --> 00:02:22,133
Due to his physical state

53
00:02:22,133 --> 00:02:24,783
an interview seems unlikely.

54
00:02:24,782 --> 00:02:28,862
But he will be out here tomorrow.

55
00:02:28,862 --> 00:02:31,712
He will come out and
explain everything.

56
00:02:31,712 --> 00:02:35,142
And the real conspirator
will be revealed!

57
00:02:35,142 --> 00:02:37,612
We will see you again
at this hour tomorrow.

58
00:02:42,551 --> 00:02:44,841
- Did you know about this?
- Not at all.

59
00:02:44,841 --> 00:02:47,171
What is he going to do?

60
00:02:47,942 --> 00:02:51,302
<i>[Food poisoning case was staged.]</i>

61
00:02:51,301 --> 00:02:52,771
What is this?

62
00:02:53,591 --> 00:02:55,801
How did this happen?

63
00:02:55,801 --> 00:02:57,171
I made sure of it, but...

64
00:02:57,171 --> 00:02:58,011
I'm sorry.

65
00:02:58,011 --> 00:02:59,501
Did you confirm it yourself?

66
00:02:59,501 --> 00:03:01,501
I didn't.

67
00:03:03,350 --> 00:03:05,910
Did you try to get in touch with him?

68
00:03:05,910 --> 00:03:08,230
He was homeless,
so he didn't have contact information.

69
00:03:08,230 --> 00:03:11,410
Are you saying you didn't
confirm anything yet?

70
00:03:11,409 --> 00:03:14,189
Why bother to confirm anything?

71
00:03:20,250 --> 00:03:23,610
It's clear that you
were behind all this.

72
00:03:23,609 --> 00:03:24,979
Kim Ji Hyuk.

73
00:03:24,979 --> 00:03:27,929
You forced someone to drink
rotten milk, huh?

74
00:03:27,929 --> 00:03:31,489
People wouldn't do that
even to a homeless mutt.

75
00:03:31,489 --> 00:03:33,799
Is that something a person could do?

76
00:03:33,798 --> 00:03:36,308
What are you talking about?

77
00:03:36,829 --> 00:03:39,419
Are you that afraid of me?

78
00:03:39,419 --> 00:03:42,649
You had to do all that
to crush me, huh?

79
00:03:42,648 --> 00:03:44,958
I feel sorry for you.

80
00:03:44,958 --> 00:03:46,598
You're out of your mind, aren't you?

81
00:03:46,598 --> 00:03:48,458
Just wait, Kang Dong Suk.

82
00:03:48,458 --> 00:03:52,658
By tomorrow, everybody will know
what kind of person you are.

83
00:03:52,657 --> 00:03:56,487
Everybody will point
their fingers at you.

84
00:03:57,157 --> 00:03:59,467
even your servant.

85
00:04:02,407 --> 00:04:04,937
Look forward to tomorrow.

86
00:04:08,966 --> 00:04:11,446
Go now to check on the homeless guy.

87
00:04:11,446 --> 00:04:13,566
Yes, I will.

88
00:04:13,566 --> 00:04:16,276
Go confirm it with your own eyes.

89
00:04:17,146 --> 00:04:19,126
Yes, sir.

90
00:04:25,666 --> 00:04:28,546
Yes, did you find his whereabout yet?

91
00:04:28,546 --> 00:04:30,016
Where is he?

92
00:04:30,015 --> 00:04:32,125
Got it.

93
00:04:58,224 --> 00:04:59,394
What happened?

94
00:04:59,394 --> 00:05:01,154
Did they really take him?

95
00:05:01,154 --> 00:05:02,824
They couldn't have
found him that easily.

96
00:05:02,823 --> 00:05:04,263
It's impossible.

97
00:05:04,264 --> 00:05:07,024
Even an excellent cop would
have taken a day or two...

98
00:05:07,024 --> 00:05:08,934
by any chance

99
00:05:08,933 --> 00:05:11,223
would Kim Ji Hyuk?

100
00:05:21,193 --> 00:05:22,583
No one is here.

101
00:05:22,583 --> 00:05:24,143
I hope I'm wrong.

102
00:05:24,142 --> 00:05:26,452
What do you think Kim Ji Hyuk did?

103
00:05:26,452 --> 00:05:28,092
Cops often use that...

104
00:05:28,093 --> 00:05:29,743
When there is no evidence or witness

105
00:05:29,743 --> 00:05:31,873
they bluff.

106
00:05:31,873 --> 00:05:33,493
- Bluff?
- Yes.

107
00:05:33,492 --> 00:05:36,322
They say they have the witness
who will testify against you.

108
00:05:36,322 --> 00:05:38,012
- They bluff like that.
- Then what?

109
00:05:38,012 --> 00:05:40,572
Then the suspect gets nervous, so...

110
00:05:40,572 --> 00:05:43,082
he tries to find the witness, right?

111
00:05:43,082 --> 00:05:45,492
Then they follow him.

112
00:05:46,541 --> 00:05:48,671
He's the one, right?

113
00:05:49,791 --> 00:05:51,561
Yes, you're right.

114
00:05:51,561 --> 00:05:53,971
Wait a second.

115
00:05:55,761 --> 00:05:58,141
Damn it.

116
00:05:58,891 --> 00:06:01,251
You suffered from food
poisoning, right?

117
00:06:10,890 --> 00:06:14,030
Could you excuse us?

118
00:06:14,030 --> 00:06:16,980
I have to talk to him privately.

119
00:06:23,670 --> 00:06:26,330
Oh my.

120
00:06:26,329 --> 00:06:28,589
You, seriously.

121
00:06:40,739 --> 00:06:45,169
They made you drink the
rotten milk, didn't they?

122
00:06:45,168 --> 00:06:47,028
Think carefully.

123
00:06:47,029 --> 00:06:50,309
They didn't treat you
like a human being.

124
00:06:50,308 --> 00:06:52,618
You were given money, right?

125
00:06:53,168 --> 00:06:57,518
They think they can do
anything with money.

126
00:06:59,007 --> 00:07:01,447
To you, I...

127
00:07:01,447 --> 00:07:04,847
I will offer you something you
really need rather than money.

128
00:07:06,838 --> 00:07:10,068
You're living apart from
your family, right?

129
00:07:10,067 --> 00:07:14,097
I will help you reunite your family.

130
00:07:14,097 --> 00:07:19,187
I will help you, so they will
never treat you like an animal again.

131
00:07:19,186 --> 00:07:21,426
I promise you that.

132
00:07:35,916 --> 00:07:37,706
What's wrong?

133
00:07:39,596 --> 00:07:41,536
Are you okay?

134
00:07:41,535 --> 00:07:43,535
Hold on. I will go to the pharmacy.

135
00:08:18,803 --> 00:08:20,803
<i>[We welcome you to Hyung Sung Distributions]</i>

136
00:08:36,083 --> 00:08:39,613
Yes, I received the money.

137
00:08:39,613 --> 00:08:41,203
By the way

138
00:08:41,202 --> 00:08:44,682
are the kids okay?

139
00:08:52,731 --> 00:08:55,101
Sir, time is up.

140
00:08:55,101 --> 00:08:57,531
The reporters are outside.
What do you want me to do?

141
00:09:00,091 --> 00:09:02,651
Okay, I will make them leave.

142
00:09:02,651 --> 00:09:06,281
Gosh, it will make the image
of our company even worse.

143
00:09:06,281 --> 00:09:08,321
As for the reporters,
I will get back to you in a minute.

144
00:09:08,321 --> 00:09:11,081
That's not what I'm here for.

145
00:09:12,221 --> 00:09:14,531
What can I do for you?

146
00:09:16,400 --> 00:09:19,750
By any chance, you...

147
00:09:19,750 --> 00:09:21,860
Someone like me

148
00:09:21,860 --> 00:09:24,970
can I be hired here?

149
00:09:29,069 --> 00:09:31,229
Of course, you can.

150
00:09:31,230 --> 00:09:33,640
You can work here.

151
00:09:33,640 --> 00:09:36,330
with me, for the rest of your life.

152
00:09:38,320 --> 00:09:41,950
Is it true what President
Kim said yesterday?

153
00:09:41,948 --> 00:09:43,728
Yes.

154
00:09:43,729 --> 00:09:46,269
It is true.

155
00:09:46,269 --> 00:09:49,649
That day, someone came up to me.

156
00:09:49,649 --> 00:09:51,759
He handed over the milk.

157
00:09:51,758 --> 00:09:55,658
He told me to drink it and go...

158
00:09:55,658 --> 00:09:59,888
He told me go buy one
more milk at the mart.

159
00:09:59,888 --> 00:10:04,388
I took the money and...

160
00:10:04,387 --> 00:10:07,267
did what he asked me to do.

161
00:10:07,268 --> 00:10:09,928
I'm sorry.

162
00:10:10,477 --> 00:10:17,777
I will go down to the police
station to report all this.

163
00:10:17,777 --> 00:10:19,097
Hey!

164
00:10:19,097 --> 00:10:20,297
Find the cop who will be
handling this case, and...

165
00:10:20,297 --> 00:10:22,877
bribe him right away.

166
00:10:28,397 --> 00:10:31,697
I heard that your son, Dong
Suk is getting married.

167
00:10:31,696 --> 00:10:33,316
Is it true?

168
00:10:33,316 --> 00:10:34,586
Yes.

169
00:10:34,586 --> 00:10:37,196
Oh my, which family is she from?

170
00:10:37,196 --> 00:10:39,406
I'm so curious.

171
00:10:39,405 --> 00:10:41,815
Well, it's just that...

172
00:10:41,815 --> 00:10:43,815
Tell us, please.

173
00:10:43,816 --> 00:10:46,236
What powerful family is she from?

174
00:10:46,236 --> 00:10:47,656
Later.

175
00:10:47,655 --> 00:10:49,845
That's good.

176
00:10:50,585 --> 00:10:54,315
- Thank you.
- Sure.

177
00:10:56,055 --> 00:10:57,425
Who is she?

178
00:10:57,425 --> 00:11:00,085
She is...

179
00:11:00,085 --> 00:11:04,285
Ah, she works at our company.

180
00:11:04,875 --> 00:11:07,915
Let's cheers.

181
00:11:10,995 --> 00:11:14,275
- Congratulations.
- Thank you.

182
00:11:16,434 --> 00:11:18,434
Thank you.

183
00:11:21,154 --> 00:11:23,814
This tastes so good.

184
00:11:23,814 --> 00:11:26,474
<i>The future I dreamed of</i>

185
00:11:26,473 --> 00:11:28,863
<i>was it becoming that woman?</i>

186
00:11:39,103 --> 00:11:40,893
Mi Ra.

187
00:11:42,132 --> 00:11:43,622
Honey.

188
00:11:43,623 --> 00:11:48,623
Honey, what's wrong?

189
00:11:48,622 --> 00:11:50,032
Wake up.

190
00:11:50,032 --> 00:11:51,402
Mi Ra, what are you doing?

191
00:11:51,402 --> 00:11:53,612
Call the doctor now!

192
00:11:53,612 --> 00:11:56,252
Honey.

193
00:11:56,252 --> 00:11:59,062
Honey, what is it?

194
00:11:59,062 --> 00:12:01,192
Honey.

195
00:12:17,601 --> 00:12:20,381
Honey, wake up.

196
00:12:20,380 --> 00:12:21,470
Honey.

197
00:12:21,470 --> 00:12:23,470
Excuse me.

198
00:12:25,870 --> 00:12:27,890
Mi Ra.

199
00:12:27,890 --> 00:12:29,600
Is that safe?

200
00:12:37,979 --> 00:12:41,629
Did you find out who did it?

201
00:12:42,949 --> 00:12:45,559
I know who.

202
00:12:45,559 --> 00:12:50,329
The victim turned himself
in and confessed.

203
00:12:50,329 --> 00:12:53,909
But the investigation
is going very slowly.

204
00:12:54,378 --> 00:12:58,258
They probably had something
to do with it too.

205
00:12:58,258 --> 00:13:00,168
They must have.

206
00:13:01,288 --> 00:13:06,308
They have money and power.

207
00:13:08,297 --> 00:13:10,187
I'm sorry.

208
00:13:10,188 --> 00:13:13,288
You were only trying to help us.

209
00:13:13,287 --> 00:13:15,727
But still it's been proven
that it was staged, so...

210
00:13:15,727 --> 00:13:17,517
things will recover soon.

211
00:13:17,518 --> 00:13:20,698
We will find a way too.

212
00:13:20,697 --> 00:13:22,737
Okay.

213
00:13:25,867 --> 00:13:30,367
It's this hard to live by my belief.

214
00:13:30,367 --> 00:13:32,707
Cheer up.

215
00:13:32,707 --> 00:13:35,757
And you have to survive till the end.

216
00:13:35,756 --> 00:13:38,746
Someone who is following
in your footstep

217
00:13:38,747 --> 00:13:41,727
will take your glory, so...

218
00:13:41,726 --> 00:13:44,456
please keep close eyes on him.

219
00:13:45,306 --> 00:13:47,716
I will.

220
00:13:47,716 --> 00:13:53,476
I will also look forward to that day.

221
00:13:57,085 --> 00:14:00,965
It appears that the artery
to the heart was blocked.

222
00:14:00,965 --> 00:14:02,725
With surgery

223
00:14:02,725 --> 00:14:05,605
the artery has been cleared.

224
00:14:06,375 --> 00:14:08,315
Since it was a minor operation

225
00:14:08,314 --> 00:14:09,654
if you rest for about a week

226
00:14:09,654 --> 00:14:11,544
he will recover soon enough.

227
00:14:11,545 --> 00:14:13,585
Okay.

228
00:14:13,584 --> 00:14:17,234
I guess you got my heart after all.

229
00:14:17,234 --> 00:14:19,074
Fortunately, the emergency
treatment was done properly.

230
00:14:19,074 --> 00:14:21,074
That's why it was minor.

231
00:14:21,073 --> 00:14:23,503
Please pay more attention from now on.

232
00:14:23,503 --> 00:14:25,363
Who did the emergency treatment?

233
00:14:25,364 --> 00:14:27,674
Why does that matter?

234
00:14:27,674 --> 00:14:30,034
What matters is that you're safe now.

235
00:14:30,713 --> 00:14:32,923
It was Mi Ra.

236
00:14:33,443 --> 00:14:35,503
It was?

237
00:14:36,893 --> 00:14:38,813
Mi Ra.

238
00:14:38,813 --> 00:14:40,973
Yes, sir.

239
00:14:51,433 --> 00:14:53,873
Thank you.

240
00:14:53,872 --> 00:14:55,312
It's okay.

241
00:14:55,312 --> 00:14:58,142
I only did what I had to do.

242
00:15:01,922 --> 00:15:05,382
Why does my father want you
to be the chief secretary?

243
00:15:05,382 --> 00:15:06,252
After we get married

244
00:15:06,251 --> 00:15:08,581
I was going to have you stay home.

245
00:15:08,581 --> 00:15:11,341
Don't you think my
talent will be wasted?

246
00:15:11,342 --> 00:15:13,502
Your talent?

247
00:15:15,421 --> 00:15:17,981
You did a good job as
a nurse this time.

248
00:15:17,981 --> 00:15:20,961
But it's different working
in the business world.

249
00:15:21,531 --> 00:15:23,791
I want to do it.

250
00:15:23,790 --> 00:15:26,160
It's important that we
get married, but...

251
00:15:26,160 --> 00:15:29,040
I want to succeed in my career too.

252
00:15:29,390 --> 00:15:32,050
Let me do it, please.

253
00:15:34,999 --> 00:15:36,439
Just because I don't like it

254
00:15:36,440 --> 00:15:38,110
can I make you do what I want?

255
00:15:38,110 --> 00:15:40,570
It's an order from President Kang.

256
00:15:40,570 --> 00:15:43,210
I can't just go against it.

257
00:15:43,529 --> 00:15:46,359
I will do my best.

258
00:15:47,949 --> 00:15:50,409
Thank you, anyway.

259
00:15:50,409 --> 00:15:53,249
You're saving many of
my family members.

260
00:15:58,338 --> 00:16:01,148
Earlier a customer
spilled coffee there.

261
00:16:01,148 --> 00:16:03,148
Scrub there hard.

262
00:16:05,748 --> 00:16:08,878
By the way, why do I have to work here?

263
00:16:08,877 --> 00:16:10,967
Whose house do you live in now?

264
00:16:10,968 --> 00:16:12,778
I'm on it.

265
00:16:14,398 --> 00:16:17,748
Briefly I thought she was an angel...

266
00:16:17,748 --> 00:16:20,288
People don't change, okay?

267
00:16:30,006 --> 00:16:31,216
Hey.

268
00:16:31,216 --> 00:16:33,086
I think this has been more
than enough for our rent.

269
00:16:33,087 --> 00:16:34,747
- Money for food.
- Money for food?

270
00:16:34,746 --> 00:16:36,216
You're unemployed now, aren't you?

271
00:16:36,216 --> 00:16:40,016
Kim Ji Hyuk doesn't
have any money either.

272
00:16:40,016 --> 00:16:42,576
Hey, you said you'd be nice
to me for the rest of your life.

273
00:16:42,576 --> 00:16:44,786
Maybe I've been too nice to you.

274
00:16:44,786 --> 00:16:46,606
You're being cheeky.

275
00:16:46,606 --> 00:16:47,746
